The paper discusses a new family of methods for improving the accuracy of unstable classification and regression methods, which falls under the category of machine learning. The use of evolutionary algorithms to suggest smarter sampling in both the feature space and training samples suggests a focus on optimization and search algorithms, which is commonly found in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of fitness functions to assess ensembles, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The use of bagging and adaptive resampling methods suggests a focus on ensemble methods, which is commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
